Offers to Sell $221 Million of Loans Said to Be Due Today

-- B y   K r i s t e n   H a u n s s
-- 
2011-03-15T15:06:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/offers-to-sell-221-million-of-loans-said-to-be-due-today.html
An investor is seeking to buy $221
million of loans made to 24 companies in an auction today,
according to two people with knowledge of the sale.  Managers were asked to submit their offers to sell these
loans by 10:30 a.m. in  New York , said one of the people, who
declined to be identified because the talks are private.
According to the terms of the sale, the buyer reserves the right
to not buy any or all of the assets, the person said.  The investor is seeking to buy slices of $5 million, $8
million, $10 million and $15 million, the person said. Among the
names the investor is seeking to buy are $15 million of Nielsen
Finance LLCâ€™ Class B dollar term loan, $10 million of Booz Allen
Hamilton Inc. and $10 million of  DaVita Inc. (DVA) , the person said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
